voice_to_text: Police recently discovered that a woman named Lisa Carter had been living in a house in Indianapolis for nine years without paying a single dollar in rent. Ten years ago, Lisa was working for a real estate company when her boss offered her a unique deal. She could live in one of the company owned homes for free as long as she remained employed there. Lisa chose a three bedroom house and moved in. She assumed a formal lease would come later, but everything changed when her boss was sent to prison for mortgage fraud and the company collapsed. Still, Lisa stayed in the house and no one followed up. Unaware the home was occupied, the city listed it for auction. Lisa tried to buy it at a low price multiple times, but each auction was mysteriously canceled. Recently, a company from Singapore finally purchased the property. The surprising twist the new owner told CBS This Morning they want Lisa to stay. After discovering the roof had started leaking, the company offered to fix it and work out a formal lease agreement. This time, however, rent will be due, but at least Lisa gets to stay and start a new chapter legally.

voice_to_text: I merely touched the giant fossil from 2 thousand years ago, never expecting it to eerily come back to life the very next second. Upon seeing this, the staff immediately activated the ultraviolet Protection measures as this was the only thing trolls feared. However, someone deliberately spilled coffee at that moment, causing the equipment to short circuit and the UV lights that had just turned on went dark as well. When the troll discovered his hands were bound by iron chains, a surge of rage instantly welled up inside him seeing the massive creature. The laboratory workers scattered in all directions, yet by then it was already too late to run. One unfortunate worker was just a second too slow and ended up being stomped into a pulp under the trolls foot. In the chaos, I let everyone out through the back door of the laboratory. Just as we reached the exit, we saw the troll squeezing out of the passage as well. With just a slight shake of its body, the troll destroyed the hydroelectric stations pipelines. Fortunately, the troll didn't continue its rampage. It simply turned and walked into the distant forest. Soon the troll arrived at a bar. It lifted off the roof and curiously surveyed the crowd inside. The foolish humans completely oblivious to the danger, all pulled out their phones to take pictures and show off. It wasn't until the troll reached out its massive palm toward the crowd that everyone finally realized something was Terribly wrong and began fleeing in every direction. But the troll, having starved for 2,000 years, had switched into buffet mode. He tossed one lucky soul right into his mouth. The troll's actions thoroughly alarmed the military. To eliminate this monster, soldiers activated the ultraviolet lighting devices on their aircraft. The instant the light hit it, burn marks appeared on the trolls body. Seeing that ultraviolet light was effective, the soldiers prepared to continue their attack. What they didn't expect, however, was that the troll grabbed a nearby utility pole and hurled it straight at the helicopter. Watching his comrades aircraft crash, the soldier was furious and prepared to charge directly at the troll. Fortunately, I stopped him in time, which allowed the soldier to calm down. The troll, meanwhile, flashed a mocking expression before swaggering away. Through these two experiences, I realized that humans alone could never defeat the troll. Only magic could defeat magic. I LED them to a mysterious cave in its deepest recesses. I gently tapped the ground with a stone as if it were some kind of signal. After waiting a moment, a violent rumbling sound came from deep within the cave and a colossal creature rapidly approached us. As it turned out, another troll lived here. To everyone's astonishment, I was able to communicate with it telepathically. Through this connection, I conveyed to the troll our purpose for coming. The next day, I stood before the troll that had been wreaking havoc everywhere and Fired a flare gun to attract its attention. Just as the troll approached me, the other troll hiding in the snow swiftly revealed itself.

voice_to_text: A man desperate to survive smashed a priceless vase worth millions. He picked out two relatively smooth pieces, tied them to a long strip of cloth, and made a makeshift pair of sunglasses. He had been trapped in the mansion for several days. He planned to pry open the vent cover on the ceiling and escape. The falling cement dust was blocked by the sunglasses, which not only greatly improved his work efficiency, but also gave Jack hope of escaping. When he finally pried off a cement block from the ceiling, he discovered a hidden screw on the frame. Jack instinctively tried to unscrew it, but it wouldn't budge. He then hammered away the cement around the vent frame, only to find that there were 12 screws embedded inside. Clearly, these screws were used to secure the bulletproof glass. Suddenly, he saw a cleaner appear on the security monitor sitting outside the mansion taking a break. Jack saw a glimmer of hope in that moment, and without hesitation he grabbed a frying pan and began smashing the door, hoping to attract the cleaner's attention. But the door was made of steel with excellent soundproofing, and the cleaner was busy with a vacuum, so he didn't hear anything coming from inside. Jack quickly scribbled a distress note, hoping to slip it through the door gap, but the gap was too small to fit anything through. He could only watch helplessly as the cleaner left the elevator. Next, he used a metal Object to pry open a hidden room where he found food and steak. Just then, the sound of water spraying filled the house. Jack quickly dropped to the ground, drinking several mouthfuls of sweet, fresh water. Refreshed, he got back to work. He kicked off a stool leg and with a small knife carefully carved the shape of a screw, eventually making a makeshift wrench. His plan was to use this wrench to unscrew the bolts, but the next second, despair took over him.

He was shocked to see the blood on my mouth, my disheveled clothes, and my pathetic posture propped up on the floor. He rushed over to help me up. I shook my head, subtly signalling him to stay silent, then took the bank card he handed me with the PIN attached and tossed it to the man. The man took the card and didn't bother me further. Waving his hand, if that's a fake card, I have countless ways to find you. Get lost! Enduring the excruciating pain throughout my body, I limped out of that sickening place, leaning on Leo's arm. When we reached the entrance, I thanked Leo. Thanks, Buddy. I'll get this sorted and pay you back quickly. He looked at me worriedly. Don't worry about the money. It's nothing. But what happened to you, I sneered. My sister found herself a fine boyfriend. I guess I have a score to settle with her. I pulled out my phone and found the number for the restaurant's assistant general manager, Mr. Peterson. Mr. Peterson was the restaurant's actual manager, someone I had personally recruited, and he was quite loyal to me. The call connected. I wasted no words, my voice devoid of emotion. You have 10 minutes to fire a manager named Brendan Miller. Otherwise Hayes Enterprises will withdraw all investment from the restaurant. Every last cent. Mr. Peterson, on the other end, was scared shitless the moment he heard my voice. He must have heard the weakness and the unusual edge in my voice as he agreed in quick, terrified succession. Not even daring to ask why, I hung up the phone and without a moment's pause, told Leo to take me straight to the police station. With the clearest, calmest logic, I recounted everything that had just happened to the officer who assisted me. After giving a detailed statement at the police station, I went to the hospital for an injury assessment. I held that thin report in my hand, and the fury of betrayal, as if fueled by hot oil, burned hotter and fiercer within me. I needed an explanation. I needed Serena Hayes to give me an explanation herself. My assistant found out Serena was at her villa. My driver and bodyguards arrived, and we headed straight for Serena's place. That villa was also a gift for me. However, when I arrived, I was greeted by blaring heavy metal music and the raucous sounds of men and women echoing through the doors and windows. She was throwing a party. No wonder she hadn't answered my calls. The villa's main door was ajar, and on a strange impulse, I didn't push it open immediately. Soon I heard a familiar male voice. It was Brendan Miller. He was pouring out his story to everyone, painting himself as a poor, helpless victim bullied by an arrogant third party, EMI, who then had the audacity to turn the tables and accuse him. I just asked him to pay the Bill, and he threw $2 million in my face, then found people to get me fired. Serena, he's gone too far. He doesn't respect you at all. He just wants to humiliate me. He just wants us to break up. Inside, Serena's circle of friends, mostly hangers on and troublemakers, echoed his outrage. Serena, in turn, was loudly comforting Brendan in her arms, her voice full of Tenderness and indulgence. Brendan, don't worry, I won't let you suffer this injustice. Then, as if to prove her resolve, she promised everyone confidently, when I get my hands on my brother, I'll make him beg for your forgiveness on his knees. Inside, those spoiled brats were still backing Brendan, shouting about how they would make me pay. Serena, just say the word and we'll go drag that bastard out right now! Yeah, let him know who truly owns this place! I couldn't listen anymore. I raised a hand and my bodyguard kicked open the villa's front door. The booming music screeched to a halt, the noisy laughter instantly vanishing. Dozens of stunned eyes all at once turn towards the doorway. No need to drag me out, I'm right here. Who wants to teach me a lesson? How to read part 2? Type the lower left corner of the video. Download it. Search my code to follow.

He steps out of the closet, slips into Anna's bed. And wraps his arms around her as she sleeps. Anna knows everything, and without protest, she quietly accepts his presence. The two of them, in their strange, silent understanding, are finally alone.

voice_to_text: My parents filed a lawsuit over my house. When I asked, my dad said, it belongs to your sister. But I showed them every deposit and one in court. Growing up, I Learned early that fairness wasn't something our family believed in. My sister Lily got everything. Ballet lessons that cost hundreds a month, a brand new Honda at 16. College tuition paid in full without her lifting a finger. Me, I got a bus pass and a lecture about building character. When I asked for help with community college costs, dad said I'd appreciate my education more if I earned it myself. So I did. I worked weekends at a grocery store, picked up night shifts at a warehouse, took out loans I'm still paying off. Every dollar I made went toward tuition or rent or keeping myself fed. Meanwhile, Lily posted Instagram photos from spring break trips I could never afford. But I kept grinding. Got my engineering degree, landed a solid job, and started saving obsessively. No fancy dinners, no vacations, no new clothes, unless the old ones had holes. For five straight years, I funneled every bonus, every overtime check, every tax refund into one account. My house fund. When I finally had enough for a down payment, I found a small two bedroom condo on the edge of town. Nothing fancy, but it was mine. I called mom crying when my offer got accepted. She actually seemed happy for me. Threw me a little Celebration. Dinner that weekend. Lily showed up late, sat in the corner stirring her wine glass. Must be nice having that engineering salary, she muttered. Some of us are still paying off grad school. I tried to ignore the sting. Mom changed the subject quickly. The day I closed on the condo, dad came by to see it. Walked through every room, nodded slowly. Smart investment if you did it right, he said. I thought that was his version of being proud. Two weeks later, a process server knocked on my door. Legal paper. My parents were suing me for the house. I called dad immediately, hands shaking. What is this? His voice was cold. Matter of fact, that house belongs to your sister. Your mother and I discussed this with our attorney. The down payment came from inheritance money that was meant for Lily's first home. I felt like I've been punched. What inheritance? Grandma split everything equally. I never touched that money. Every cent for this house came from my paychecks. You're making this more complicated than it needs to be, he said. Lily needs that house more than you do. She's planning for it. You can buy another one later. I hung up and immediately called my bank. Pulled every statement from the last five years. Every deposit had a clear paper trail. Payroll transfers, direct deposits. Nothing from any inheritance account. When we got to court, their lawyer painted this picture of a greedy daughter who'd stolen Her sister's dream. Dad took the stand first. Confident and calm. He testified about a long standing family understanding that grandma's inheritance money was earmarked for Lily's first home purchase. Mom went next, dabbing her eyes with a tissue. Talked about how much Lily had sacrificed, how she didn't make as much money as me, how unfair it was that I'd used family money to get ahead. She made it sound like I'd robbed them. Lily sat at their table looking wounded, like betrayed her somehow. A few relatives in the gallery nodded along sympathetically. Then my lawyer stood up. She presented a thick folder to the judge. Five years of pay stubs. Every single one. Transfer records showing money moving from my employer directly to my personal savings account. Bank statements with highlighted deposits, each one labeled and dated tax returns.
